nodes.text: The C-73 Tracker starfighter was a starfighter produced by Sublight Products Corporation that predated the Z-95 Headhunter.
The C-73 was relatively slow and unmaneuverable and was armed with a pair of wing-tipped laser cannons.

This fighter was one of the last designs of Subpro Corporation before beginning a partnership with Incom Corporation for the Z-95 Headhunter project. The Separatists employed these craft in the crisis leading up to the Clone Wars. During the Imperial era, it continued to see use, but in limited quantity. Even older than the Z-95 Headhunter, it was mostly considered an antique, with some units in the Imperial Stardrive Museum of Coruscant. Around 2 ABY, it was only used by the m'Yalfor'ac Order of Guiteica as part of the planetary defense force.
